wiki.summary: “44 BullDog” is the fourth track from Pop Smoke’s posthumous debut album Shoot for the Stars, Aim for the Moon. The track is named after the Charter Arms Bulldog, a 5-shot traditional double-action revolver available for the .44 Special and .357 Magnum cartridges, which Pop raps about on the hook. The song is produced by MoraBeats and MobzBeatz, known for co-producing the track “Gatti.” The instrumental is originally from Nito NB’s Lightwork Freestyle and was also used in Nas Blixky’s “No Cap.” Read more on Last.fm.
